<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Recall" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Recall,</orth> 1) to call back: <cit><quote>in rage sent out, --ed in rage,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1671" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1671</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ed from their exile,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.4.155" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. V, 4, 155</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wt 3.2.157" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 2, 157</bibl>. <cit><quote>--ed to life again,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.66" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 66</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>r. his life,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.61" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 61</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to revoke, to annul by a subsequent act: <cit><quote>passed sentence may not be --ed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.148" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 148</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>r. not what we give,</quote> <bibl n="shak. per 3.1.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. III, 1, 25</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>